\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 18. B. riparius} Rehmann,{\i  Notizbl. Veg. Gest. Schwarz. Meer} 83 (1872) ({\i B. fibrosus} Hackel, {\i B. erectus} auct. ross., non Hudson). Densely caespitose, sometimes with very short rhizomes; stems 30-90 cm, slender, erect or decumbent at the base. Leaves 10-20 cm × 2-3 mm, flaccid, scabrid, the margins sometimes with brittle cilia; sheaths with long, patent or retrorse hairs, the basal decaying into persistent, reticulate fibres. Panicle 10-20 × 3-7 cm, erect, rather lax, the branches scabrid, each with 1-2 spikelets; spikelets 20-30 mm, lanceolate, usually pale green, with 5-7 florets. Lower glume 8-10 mm, the upper 9-12 mm. Lemma 11-13 mm, oblong-lanceolate, usually glabrous, sometimes appressed-hairy; awn 5-8 mm, straight or slightly curved. Palea shorter than lemma. Anthers 2·5-3·5 mm. 2n = 70.{\i  Meadows, scrub and rocky hillsides. S.E. Europe, extending northwards to C. Russia}. Bu Gr Ju Rm Rs (C, W, K, E).
\par

