\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 21. B. pseudosecalinus} P.M. Sm.,{\i  Feddes Repert.}{\b  77}: 63 (1968). Stems 30-60 cm, erect, slender; sheaths hairy. Panicle 5-10 cm, lax, contracted and somewhat nodding after flowering; spikelets 8-12 mm, lanceolate at first, becoming ovate, glabrous, disarticulating tardily at maturity; florets imbricate at first, erecto-patent after anthesis. Glumes and lemmas corneous, obscurely veined; lemma 5-6 mm, the bluntly angled margins becoming inrolled, revealing the rhachilla; awn 2-6 mm, straight or slightly flexuous. Palea shorter than lemma. Anthers 1·25-1·75 mm. Grain 4-4·5 mm, longitudinally incurved at maturity. 2n = 14. •{\i  Britain and Ireland.} Br Hb.
